---
title: Soleur AI Agents
description: "AI agents for business — engineering, marketing, legal, finance, operations, product, sales, and support. Each agent is a specialist in the Soleur company-as-a-service platform."
layout: base.njk
permalink: pages/agents.html
---

    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Soleur AI Agents</h1>
        <p>{{ stats.agents }} AI agents across {{ stats.departments }} business departments — from code review and architecture to marketing strategy, legal compliance, and financial planning.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="prose">

Agentic engineering treats AI agents as specialist team members, not generic assistants. Each Soleur agent is trained for a specific business function &mdash; code review, brand strategy, legal compliance, financial reporting, competitive intelligence, and more. Together, they form a company-as-a-service organization that operates across {{ stats.departments }} departments with the depth of dedicated specialists.

What separates this from running {{ stats.departments }} disconnected tools is cross-domain coherence. Every agent shares context through a compounding knowledge base. The brand guide informs marketing copy. Competitive analysis shapes product positioning. Legal audits reference the privacy policy. A decision in one domain propagates to every other domain that depends on it.

The result: {{ stats.agents }} agents that function as a unified AI organization, not a collection of isolated capabilities. Explore the departments below to see what each agent does.

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="container">
      <nav class="category-nav" aria-label="Agent categories">
        {%- for domain in agents.domains %}
        <a href="pages/agents.html#{{ domain.key }}" class="category-pill">{{ domain.name }}</a>
        {%- endfor %}
      </nav>

      {%- for domain in agents.domains %}
      <section id="{{ domain.key }}" class="category-section">
        <div class="category-header">
          <h2 class="category-title">{{ domain.name }}</h2>
          <span class="category-count">{{ domain.count }} agent{{ "s" if domain.count != 1 }}</span>
        </div>

        {%- if domain.subcategories.length > 0 %}
          {%- for sub in domain.subcategories %}
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-base); color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">{{ sub.name }}</h3>
        <div class="catalog-grid">
            {%- for agent in sub.agents %}
          <article class="component-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <span class="card-dot" style="background: {{ domain.cssVar }}"></span>
              <span class="card-category">{{ domain.name }} / {{ sub.name }}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title">{{ agent.name }}</h3>
            <p class="card-description">{{ agent.description }}</p>
          </article>
            {%- endfor %}
        </div>
          {%- endfor %}
        {%- else %}
        <div class="catalog-grid">
          {%- for agent in domain.agents %}
          <article class="component-card">
            <div class="card-header">
              <span class="card-dot" style="background: {{ domain.cssVar }}"></span>
              <span class="card-category">{{ domain.name }}</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="card-title">{{ agent.name }}</h3>
            <p class="card-description">{{ agent.description }}</p>
          </article>
          {%- endfor %}
        </div>
        {%- endif %}
      </section>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
